commit.message:
improve performance for computing id (#1332)

Refactors the logic to create the complete id string
before feeding into the UTF-8 encoder and then message
digest. For the existing benchmark this change improves
the throughput by ~33%.

commit.message:
reduce allocations for computing ids (#1331)

Eliminates most of the allocations for computing ids from
the tag maps. In particular, the buffers, message digest,
UTF-8 encoder, and string array now get reused. It also
uses a custom sort so the tuple allocations can be avoided
and just use pairs of strings in an array.

commit.message:
more efficient empty check for hash map (#1330)

Updates the SmallHashMap implementation to override
the `isEmpty` method with an efficient check. The
default that is inherited will allocate an iterator.

commit.message:
limit gh-actions to the main repo (#1328)

Previously, when maintaining a fork of this repo, merging updates from
the upstream would trigger GitHub actions for the snapshot workflow,
which failed because the secrets are missing. We do not want forks to
run either the snapshot or the release actions.
